  "response": "Yes, there are legal requirements for reporting suspected money laundering in many countries. Financial institutions, businesses, and professionals in certain industries are typically required to:\n\n1. Conduct customer due diligence\n2. Report suspicious transactions\n3. Maintain transaction records\n4. Implement anti-money laundering (AML) compliance programs\n\nSpecific reporting requirements vary by jurisdiction, but generally involve notifying financial intelligence units or relevant authorities about potential money laundering activities.",
